CNCP v1 23305
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7478: `toRaw` has wrong typing for `DeepReadonly` array",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:12.450188+00:00",
  "text": "`toRaw` has wrong typing for `DeepReadonly` array\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.45\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nNo need\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport {DeepReadonly, readonly, Ref, ref, toRaw} from \"vue\";\r\n\r\n\r\ntype TypeA = {a: string};\r\n\r\n// Fine\r\nconst a1: Ref<TypeA>           = ref({a: \"a1\"});\r\nconst b1: Readonly<Ref<TypeA>> = readonly(a1);\r\nconst c1: TypeA                = toRaw(b1.value); // OK\r\n\r\n// Not fine\r\nconst a2: Ref<TypeA[]>               = ref([{a: \"a1\"}, {a: \"a2\"}]);\r\nconst b2: DeepReadonly<Ref<TypeA[]>> = readonly(a2);\r\nconst c2: TypeA[]                    = toRaw(b2.value) /* as TypeA[] */; // TS4104 Error\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\n`toRaw` returns `TypeA[]` type for `c2`.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n```\r\nTS4104: The type 'readonly { readonly a: string; }[]' is 'readonly' and cannot be assigned to the mutable type 'TypeA[]'.\r\n```\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nOS: Windows 10\r\nNode: 18.12.1\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n`toRaw` actually works as expected, but there is the problem with typing.\r\nIt forces me to additionally use `as TypeA[]` [*](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/2/everyday-types.html#type-assertions).",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: reactivity",
    "scope: types"
  ],
